The paper discusses multiagent decision-making problems in partially observable environments, which are typically studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), multiagent systems (cs.MA), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on a new formalism called Factored-Observation Games (FOGs), which can be used to model extensive-form games (EFGs) and partially observable stochastic games (POSGs). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.AI, cs.GT, and cs.LG, followed by cs.MA and cs.SY.
